verbose_text: Akbay et al. [XREF_BIBR] compared RBP4, retinol and TTR levels in diabetic and healthy BMI matched subjects; they found no differences between those who had retinopathy of macrovascular disease, with lower values of all three markers associated to micro and macro-albuminuria, concluding that retinopathy and cardiovascular disease are not related to RBP4 status.
